description.narrative: 4.3 The selected municipalities develop and implement, at the municipal level, results-based management and accountability tools with a children's rights- and gender-based approach, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Public Finance And Local Governance, Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 4. By 2021, the context of social policies is based on a rights-based approach and takes gender differences into account, as well as placing an emphasis on children who suffer exclusion

description.narrative: The Model of Incentives for the national certification of municipalities, along with the municipal investment guidelines and the measurement of municipal Public Investment in Children and Adolescents (IpNA), marks a paradigm shift in working with municipalities. An average of 96 municipalities have already been trained in these instruments, which will be operating starting in 2022. In the context of transition to a new government administration, an agreement to deepen and continue SIGADENAH was signed by the mayors of the selected municipalities. | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/01/2022
